flowRoot.flowPara: If the user is an administrator, the whole disk is displayed, including space used by other users. Standard user accounts are only shown an analysis of the space they have used.
Directories in the current path are shown at the top of the sidebar list and allow navigating back.
- User accounts (shown if the user is admin)
* Pinned to the top and selected by default
Trash, Downloads, XDG folders, Applications can be opened and their contents examined. Other items show an information popover.
Selecting a top level item selects all its content for removal - it acts as a select all/none toggle.
Cached files make some operations faster and help to reduce the amount of data that is downloaded. Cached files can be safely removed and will be gradually replaced afterwards.
Operating system files are an essential part of your system and cannot be removed.
Files belonging to other users can be deleted by removing their user accounts from Settings.
Root and home partitions - initial state
Music will be removed and will have to be downloaded and installed to be used again.
Uninstalled popover (shown for apps that aren't installed, but which have data left over):
